title: Google DeepMind's achievement at the International Mathematical Olympiad (IMO)
summary: Discusses the significance of AlphaProof and AlphaGeometry2 solving 4 out of 6 IMO problems, achieving a top silver medal performance. Highlights the implications for AI development and the race towards AGI.

title: The myth of unstructured data
summary: Matt shares an article he wrote five years ago about the concept of unstructured data, suggesting it's a myth. He invites readers to read the article and share their perspectives.

title: AI training techniques and parallels with human education
summary: Explores similarities between AI training methods and human educational principles, such as curriculum learning, knowledge distillation, and specialized training.

title: Small Language Models (SLMs) vs Large Language Models (LLMs)
summary: Discusses the emergence of efficient small AI models from Apple and Microsoft, highlighting their advantages in privacy, efficiency, and accessibility.

title: Moshi, a speech-to-speech AI model
summary: Announces the release of Moshi by Kyutai, a French non-profit, beating larger tech companies in releasing the first speech-to-speech model to the market.

title: Singapore's GenAI Ecosystem event (group post)
summary: Matt shares his experience at an industry event discussing Singapore's GenAI Ecosystem and mentions Temus' GenAI talent management platform, TalentForge.

title: Singapore's GenAI Ecosystem event (public version)
summary: Similar to the previous post but shared publicly, discussing the GenAI Ecosystem event and Temus' TalentForge platform.

title: SpaceX Starship test flight
summary: Describes the fourth test flight of SpaceX's Starship, highlighting its achievements and challenges during the flight.

title: AI's superiority in early detection of breast cancer
summary: Discusses a UK trial where an AI tool named Mia outperformed expert radiologists in detecting breast cancer cases.

title: The potential AI apocalypse
summary: Matt argues that the real concern isn't AI itself, but how humans will use and distribute the benefits of AI technology.
